). Among the inpatients who used PPIs or H2RAs concomitantly with <italic>C. difficile</italic>-targeted antibiotics during the treatment phase, 380 (54%) used a PPI, 55 (8%) used an H2RA, and 12 (2%) used both. During the follow-up period, 389 (55%) of inpatients used PPIs and/or H2RAs. Among inpatients who used these drugs during the follow-up period, 353 (50%) used a PPI, 54 (8%) used an H2RA and 18 (3%) used both.</p><table-wrap id="BMJGAST2014000028TB2" orientation="portrait" position="float"><label>Table&#x000a0;2</label><caption><p>PPI and H2RA use during phase 3 studies (mITT inpatients, n=701)</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><colgroup span="1"><col align="left" span="1"/><col align="char" char="." span="1"/><col align="char" char="." span="1"/><col align="char" char="." span="1"/></colgroup><thead valign="bottom"><tr><th rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">PPI</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">H2RA</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">PPI/H2RA</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan="4" rowspan="1">FDX (n=341)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;Pretreatment</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">152/303 (50.17%)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">17/39 (43.59%)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">168/339 (49.56%)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;Day 1 of treatment</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">173/344 (50.29%)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">20/48 (41.67%)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">191/388 (49.23%)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;Treatment (days 1&#x02013;10)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">198/380 (52.11%)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">23/55 (41.82%)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">215/423 (50.83%)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;Follow-up (days 11&#x02013;40)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">186/353 (52.69%)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">19/54 (35.19%)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">196/389 (50.39%)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan=